'''天主教會性侵害案例'''是在20世纪和21世纪，涉及{{Link-en|天主教会的神父|Priesthood in the Catholic Church|天主教神父}}、[[修女|修女]]和{{Link-en|天主教徒性虐待案件|Abuse by members of Catholic orders|信徒}}的[[兒童性虐待|儿童性虐待案件]]以及随后的掩盖事件导致了大量的指控、调查、审判与定罪。遭受性虐待的受害者包括男孩和女孩，最小的受害者年仅3岁，而大部分的受害者年龄介于11岁到14岁之间<ref name=hundreds>{{cite news|agency = [[Associated_Press|Associated Press]] | title=Hundreds of priests shuffled worldwide, despite abuse allegations |date=2004-06-20 | work=[[USA_Today|USA Today]] | url = https://www.usatoday.com/news/religion/2004-06-19-church-abuse_x.htm}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Stephens |first=Scott |title=Catholic sexual abuse study greeted with incurious contempt |url=http://www.abc.net.au/religion/articles/2011/05/27/3229135.htm |accessdate=2012-07-23 |newspaper=ABC Religion and Ethics |date=2011-05-27 |archive-date=2018-09-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180906012916/http://www.abc.net.au/religion/articles/2011/05/27/3229135.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Lattin|first=Don|title=$30 Million Awarded Men Molested by `Family Priest' / 3 bishops accused of Stockton coverup|url=http://www.sfgate.com/news/article/30-Million-Awarded-Men-Molested-by-Family-3001550.php|accessdate=2012-07-23|newspaper=[[San_Francisco_Chronicle|San Francisco Chronicle]]|date=1998-07-17|quote=Attorney Jeff Anderson said the Howard brothers were repeatedly molested between 1978 and 1991, from age 3 to 13.|archive-date=2020-12-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201211025855/https://www.sfgate.com/news/article/30-Million-Awarded-Men-Molested-by-Family-3001550.php|dead-url=no}}<br />Reverend Oliver O'Grady later confessed to the abuse of many other children. The documentary ''Deliver Us from Evil'' explored his story and the cover-up by Diocesan officials.</ref><ref>Bush R. & Wardell H.S. 1900, ''Stoke Industrial School, Nelson (Report of Royal Commission On, Together With Correspondence, Evidence and Appendix)'' Government Printer; Wellington, 8.</ref>。

从1980年代开始，这些指控开始受到新闻界零星、孤立的报道。其中许多案件涉及的是针对十几年前性虐待的指控；例如在性虐待行为发生多年之后，长大成人的成年人或大龄青年经常会提出这样的起诉。还有一些案件涉及[[天主教会圣统制|天主教会的高层人员]]，他们被指控掩盖了有关性虐待罪行的投诉或控诉，并将性虐待的神父转移到其他[[教区|教区]]，这造成其可以继续从事性虐待行为<ref name="Bruni, p.336">{{cite book|last=Bruni|first=Frank|title=A Gospel of Shame: Children, Sexual Abuse, and the Catholic Church |url=https://archive.org/details/gospelofshamechi00brun|publisher=HarperCollins |year=2002 |isbn=0060522321}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | date = 2010-06-29 | title = Sex abuse victim accuses Catholic church of fraud | work = [[USA_Today|USA Today]] | url = https://www.usatoday.com/news/religion/2010-06-24-fraud23_ST_N.htm | accessdate = 2012-06-24 | archive-date = 2011-10-24 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20111024225917/http://www.usatoday.com/news/religion/2010-06-24-fraud23_ST_N.htm | dead-url = no }}</ref>。

到了1990年代之后，这些案件开始得到主流媒体和公众的关注，特别是在[[爱尔兰|爱尔兰]]、[[加拿大|加拿大]]、[[美国|美国]]和[[澳大利亚|澳大利亚]]。1996年，澳大利亚教会就此采取了全新的宗教礼仪并纠正错误<ref>[http://www.abc.net.au/religion/stories/s956918.htm Meet George Pell, Australia's Newest Cardinal] {{Wayback|url=http://www.abc.net.au/religion/stories/s956918.htm |date=20180404052916 }}; www.abc.net.au;  2003-10-21</ref>。随着民众意识的增强，[[教宗|教宗]]在随后就此进行了道歉。在2001年的致歉中，[[若望·保祿二世|若望·保祿二世]]称发生在天主教会内的性虐待事件是“对[[耶稣基督|耶稣基督]]见证与教导的深重抵触”<ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/europe/1671540.stm Pope sends first e-mail apology] {{Wayback|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/europe/1671540.stm |date=20200727185430 }}; http://news.bbc.co.uk {{Wayback|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/ |date=20080414035024 }}; 2001-11-23</ref>。[[本笃十六世|本笃十六世]]面见了受害者并当面致歉，他表示对虐待罪行的“羞辱”和呼吁将肇事者绳之以法，同时他也谴责了教会当局的不当处理<ref>[http://www.abc.net.au/news/2008-07-19/pope-deeply-sorry-for-evil-of-child-abuse/444788 Pope Deeply Sorry for Child Abuse] {{Wayback|url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/2008-07-19/pope-deeply-sorry-for-evil-of-child-abuse/444788 |date=20210225185058 }}; www.abc.net.au; 2008-07-19</ref><ref>[https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/europe/vaticancityandholysee/7489455/Popes-apology-You-have-suffered-grievously-and-I-am-truly-sorry.html Pope's Apology: 'You have suffered grievously and I am truly sorry'] {{Wayback|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/europe/vaticancityandholysee/7489455/Popes-apology-You-have-suffered-grievously-and-I-am-truly-sorry.html |date=20210210211935 }}; The Telgraph; 2010-03-20</ref>。

同时天主教高层人员认为媒体的报道过于泛滥且放大了天主教性虐待案的比例，因为性虐待事件在其他宗教或教会里也时有发生<ref name="guardian">{{Cite news|last=Butt|first=Riazat|author2=Asthana, Anushka|title=Sex abuse rife in other religions, says Vatican|work=[[The_Guardian|The Guardian]]|date=2009-07-28|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2009/sep/28/sex-abuse-religion-vatican|accessdate=2009-10-10|location=London|archive-date=2013-01-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130127210125/http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/2009/sep/28/sex-abuse-religion-vatican|dead-url=no}}</ref>。1990年代的一系列电视[[纪录片|纪录片]]，例如[[UTV电视台|UTV电视台]]在1994年拍摄的《童年梦魇（{{lang|en|Suffer The Children}}）》就在爱尔兰引发全国关注<ref>MOORE, Chris, "Betrayal of Trust: The Father Brendan Smyth Affair and the Catholic Church"; Marino 1995, {{ISBN|1-86023-027-X}}; the producer's book about the programme's content</ref>。《[[波士顿环球报|波士顿环球报]]》在2002年针对天主教会性侵案所展开的一项重要调查报道引起了媒体对该类事件的广泛报道，该调查报道后来于2015年被改编成由[[湯瑪士·麥卡錫|汤姆斯·麦卡锡]]执导的电影《[[驚爆焦點|聚焦]]》。到了2010年代，绝大部分的相关报道多集中在欧洲<ref name="pewforum">{{cite news |url=http://pewforum.org/Christian/Catholic/The-Pope-Meets-the-Press--Media-Coverage-of-the-Clergy-Abuse-Scandal.aspx |title=The Pope Meets the Press: Media Coverage of the Clergy Abuse Scandal |date=2010-06-11 |accessdate=2010-09-15 |publisher=Pew Research Center |archive-date=2013-05-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130528223446/http://www.pewforum.org/Christian/Catholic/The-Pope-Meets-the-Press--Media-Coverage-of-the-Clergy-Abuse-Scandal.aspx |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="washingtonpost">{{cite news |url=http://newsweek.washingtonpost.com/onfaith/undergod/2010/06/study_looks_at_media_coverage_of_catholic_sex_abuse_scandal.html |title=Study looks at media coverage of Catholic sex abuse scandal |author=William Wan |date=2010-06-11 |accessdate=2010-09-15 |work=[[The_Washington_Post|The Washington Post]] |archive-date=2012-03-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120327111210/http://newsweek.washingtonpost.com/onfaith/undergod/2010/06/study_looks_at_media_coverage_of_catholic_sex_abuse_scandal.html |dead-url=yes }}</ref>和澳大利亚。

